<p>OpenProject 5.0.18 contains several bug fixes:</p>

<ul>
  <li>The wiki toolbar did not work. This has been fixed
(<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/23050/activity">#23050</a>).</li>
  <li>WhenÂ a project contains no members the button to add a member on the
project overview was not displayed. Also the link on the button was
wrong. This has been fixed
(<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/22970/activity">#22970</a>).</li>
  <li>Some of the links on the landing page were wrong and have been
corrected
(<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/22967/activity">#22967</a>).</li>
  <li>An error preventing exported PDFs to be opened on Mac OS X El
Capitan has been fixed
(<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/22730/activity">#22730</a>).</li>
  <li>Gravatars were not properly loaded. This has been fixed
(<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/5120/activity">#5120</a>).</li>
</ul>

<p>In addition, there are several design and usability improvements:</p>

<ul>
  <li>The styling for the documents module was missing. This has been
fixed
(<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/23158/activity">#23158</a>).</li>
  <li>Several improvements have been made to responsive / mobile layouts
(<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/22953/activity">#22953</a>,
<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/22944/activity">#22944</a>).</li>
  <li>Several design errors have been fixed
(<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/23109/activity">#23109</a>,
<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/23104/activity">#23104</a>,
<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/23052/activity">#23052</a>,
<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/23046/activity">#23046</a>,
<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/22997/activity">#22997</a>).</li>
  <li>Many accessibility improvements have been made.</li>
</ul>

<p>The textbox above a forum does now render textile. Itâ€™s therefore
possible to e.g. include links or references
(<a href="https://community.openproject.com/work_packages/23180/activity">#23180</a>).</p>

